node.title: 15 migrants, driver hurt in rollover crash after high-speed chase
node.description: Two of the injured were in critical condition after the crash in the San Antonio area.
node.content: ["San Antonio\u00a0\u2014 Fifteen migrants and another person were injured after the truck they were in rolled over following a high-speed chase with Texas deputies on Sunday, according to authorities.", "A deputy had pulled over the truck around 8 a.m. in Medina County, west of San Antonio, when one occupant fled the vehicle before it sped off, according to the Medina County Sheriff's Office. ", " The chase continued into nearby Bexar County, where the driver lost control and the truck rolled over several times. ", " Fifteen migrants were found in the truck as well as a driver, who is from Austin. ", " Two people were taken by helicopter to a San Antonio hospital and the other individuals from the truck were transported by ambulance, according to authorities. ", " Officials say two of the individuals were in critical condition. The conditions of the others weren't immediately known. ", " Authorities say the driver, whose name wasn't immediately released, had a gun in the truck and is facing several charges."]
